git pull 'remote_name' 'branch_name'

The git pull command is a combination of git fetch which fetches the recent commits in the local repository and git merge, which will merge the branch 
from a remote to a local branch also 'remote_name' is the repository name and 'branch_name' is the name of the specific branch.


Basic Branching and the Merging in the git.

https://git-scm.com/book/en/v2/Git-Branching-Basic-Branching-and-Merging

git checkout -b iss53 // equivalent to the commands $ git branch iss53 $ git checkout iss53

